name: EA-008-Kant
description:
Immanuel Kant (1724 - 1804 aC) was a Prussian philosopher. Widely regarded as the leading philosopher of the modern era, Kant operated, in epistemology, a synthesis between continental rationalism and the English empirical tradition.

Digital Watercolor Vector Illustration made in Adobe Photoshop, 1200x1200px, 200dpi, JPEG
